Dear Colmesneil ISD Community,
In light of the recent closures around us and impending heavy traffic on 69, because of mandatory evacuation orders, we are going to close school for the remainder of the week.
Please continue to check the district‚Äôs site for more information. Our prayers are for safety and protection for everyone.
text:
Dear Colmesneil ISD Community,
In light of the recent closures around us and impending heavy traffic on 69, because of mandatory evacuation orders, we are going to close school for the remainder of the week.
Please continue to check the district‚Äôs site for more information. Our prayers are for safety and protection for everyone.

post_text:
At this time, we are monitoring the weather and in contact with Tyler County Emergency Management. Please keep the District‚Äôs website, social media and Remind accounts open as will be posting updates through those outlets.
Currently we are planning on having school this week until the weather or extenuating conditions force us to do otherwise.
Again, we will keep you posted regarding closures as we receive information.

post_text:
Dear Seniors(Parents of Seniors)-
A gift from CISD to you-
The yearbook staff would like to give you a WHOLE FREE page in the yearbook to publish up to 6 pictures of yourself. If the pictures are on your phone, make sure you send the original picture(original size), do not screen shot the picture, the quality goes way down and will not be of good quality.
Include a dedication from your parent(s) if you would like, or some wise words from yourself.
Email the pictures to yearbook@colmesneilisd.net and what you would like to say. Please do not leave yourself out. We want to put YOU, SENIOR GRADUATE, in print!
By the way, send these by May 8 to yearbook@colmesneilisd.net.
